1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In today's session we are going to look at how we can improve our SEO rankings.

2
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:10,800
But what is SEO?

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,600
Search engine optimization refers to techniques that help you make your website rank higher

4
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:16,960
in search engine results.

5
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:18,760
The aim is of course to get more visitors to your site organically.

6
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:24,160
Search engines send bots to a site, to crawl through it and find out what the content is

7
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:29,200
about and where the site links to.

8
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:31,480
They also check out what the images are about, test if the site loads quickly and also investigates

9
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:37,600
if the layout of the site is accessible and good for mobile devices.

10
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:42,960
Once they are done crawling, bots figure out keywords from your site and then record

11
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:48,400
these keywords in the search engine database.

12
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:52,400
So now when anybody starts a search, search engines match a user's search query with

13
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:59,040
the keywords in the database to recommend sites that are a close match.

14
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:04,080
Let's look at some tips that we can implement.

15
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:07,360
Firstly, make your way to Settings, click on Reading and ensure that you have deselected

16
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:13,560
the search engine visibility box.

17
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:16,880
If this box is ticked, it will discourage search engines from indexing this site and

18
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:21,760
we don't want that.

19
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:23,360
This option is only used when a site is still being created.

20
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:28,400
The second thing to take note of is that search engines love sites with fresh content.

21
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:34,280
So keep your site up to date with new content as much as possible.

22
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:39,360
If your homepage and other pages really change, it is advised to have a blog page or news page

23
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:45,080
and ensure that you frequently post about your products, your brand, your clients and

24
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,760
various other topics.

25
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,400
The third tip is to make sure you have quality content on your website.

26
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:58,720
Google has published an EAT guideline which basically says that search engines look at

27
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:04,360
expertise, authority and trustworthiness.

28
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:08,480
So let's first talk about expertise.

29
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,880
Write about content you are knowledgeable and passionate about.

30
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:15,440
What about authority?

31
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:16,760
Well, if you have shown expertise, it will be viewed by search engines as authoritative

32
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,480
if others link to your site, if people talk about your site in social media and if you

33
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
link to repeatable sites in your content.

34
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:31,280
Lastly, the T stands for trustworthiness.

35
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:34,680
So make sure information that you share is trustworthy and factual.

36
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:40,840
Here is an important question you can ask yourself.

37
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:43,840
Is your content shareable?

38
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Things to consider.

39
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:47,240
Is it funny?

40
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:48,560
Is it maybe too long?

41
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:50,280
Does it have good taste?

42
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:51,880
Does it use plain language?

43
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:53,880
Does it have a summary or TL:DR at the top?

44
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:57,320
It basically comes down to making sure your content is worth reading and worth sharing.

45
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:03,040
Next, let's talk about keywords.

46
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,200
Keywords and keyword phrases in your content make it easier for people to find your site

47
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:11,640
via search engines.

48
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:13,320
A well-optimized site speaks the same language as their audience, so to speak.

49
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:19,120
We therefore need to know what folks are searching for and include those words or phrases on

50
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:24,360
our pages and in our posts.

51
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:28,160
Keyword research will help you know what keywords people search for when looking for

52
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,960
similar sites.

53
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:33,280
You can use free tools such as WordStream or Google Keyword Planner to find those keywords

54
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:39,040
that you can use in your content.

55
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:42,080
The way you would go about finding keywords is to type the domain name of sites that are

56
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:46,360
similar to yours.

57
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:49,320
This will give you a hint of what words people use to search content on that site.

58
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:55,040
Once you have identified these keywords, use them in your site's content.

59
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:00,320
Search engines will prioritize what your content is titled when they decide keywords, but you

60
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:06,120
can also use them in excerpts, headings and content.

61
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:11,160
The way it is laid out here is generally the priority in which you want to use keywords.

62
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:17,280
Remember to use keywords naturally and to avoid keyword stuffing or overusing keywords

63
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:22,440
as this will damage your SEO.

64
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:26,520
Let's talk some more about linking.

65
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:28,680
Search engines will travel through your links to understand your site structure and to look

66
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:32,360
for more content.

67
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:33,840
So link to other posts already on your site as pages that are linked multiple times are

68
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:39,280
considered more important by search engines.

69
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:44,200
Also remember to set external links to sites that are reputable and also have good EAT,

70
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:50,440
expertise, authority and trustworthiness as this will make your site more credible as

71
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:55,760
well.

72
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,840
The next topic that we want to discuss is metadata.

73
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:01,640
Metadata are tags in your page content that are visible to search engines.

74
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:06,760
It is hidden behind the scenes but it does give critical information about your site

75
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:11,640
to search engines.

76
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,240
You might not have known this but meta descriptions is the information shown below each individual

77
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:19,920
search result.

78
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,360
Metadata is automatically created by WordPress so it's not easy to edit directly.

79
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,800
But most SEO plugins allow you to edit and modify the metadata to be more geared to

80
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:34,600
your content.

81
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:36,360
Usually no more than two sentences.

82
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:40,080
One of the things you can do is write an excerpt for post as WordPress uses these excerpts to

83
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:46,200
create meta descriptions.

84
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:48,960
So it is advised to use your keywords and hand write these excerpts.

85
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:53,480
Otherwise it just takes the top paragraph from your content.

86
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:58,320
Next, site speed is important.

87
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,400
Search engines definitely look at site speed when ranking sites.

88
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:04,760
So this is an important part of SEO.

89
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,400
Here are a few considerations that will help you to improve your site speed.

90
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:13,480
Does your host rank high with regard to site speed?

91
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:16,880
Does your host have caching enabled although you can also use a caching plugin?

92
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:22,160
Is your WordPress theme quick to load?

93
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:24,400
Some very snazzy WordPress themes that uses a lot of plugins can drastically change your

94
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:28,840
site speed.

95
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:29,880
So be careful.

96
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:31,440
Have you optimized images and videos?

97
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:34,320
Have you installed well-built plugins?

98
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:37,040
And does your theme and plugins work well together?

99
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:40,320
You can investigate your site speed by using tools such as GTmetrics or PageSpeed Insights.

100
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:49,040
Image optimization is another piece of the SEO puzzle.

101
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,600
Let's first look at a few steps that you can take before uploading images to your site.

102
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:59,160
Number one, choose a good file format such as PNG, JPEG or WebP.

103
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:06,720
In this example I am using the open source website Squoosh to change the file format for

104
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:11,440
free.

105
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:12,440
It also has some other settings worth exploring.

106
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:16,640
Number two, scale the image dimensions.

107
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:19,880
Images that are too large will be resized when it shows up on people's browser and will

108
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:24,640
affect the loading speed of your site.

109
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:27,040
So make sure you shrink the dimensions of very large images as most monitors in the world

110
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:32,320
are no bigger than 1920 by 1080 pixels in size.

111
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:38,520
Luckily WordPress does make three different size variations when you upload an image but

112
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:43,560
that large image still takes space up on your server.

113
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:48,440
Number three, reduce the image file size.

114
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,800
You want to reduce the file size of images without reducing the quality.

115
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:56,320
You can use programs such as TinyPNG or also Squoosh.

116
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:01,480
And lastly, rename the image files so that it explains what the image is about.

117
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:07,960
When an image has been uploaded to WordPress it is advised to add alternative text or ALT

118
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:13,080
text and a description of the image.

119
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:16,280
Search engines place a high value on ALT text and they use this information to understand

120
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:21,120
the context of an image, what the image is about and the purpose of the image.

121
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,000
Images should also have ALT text for accessibility purposes.

122
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,400
You also want to ensure that at least one of your images has your key word or key phrase

123
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:36,680
as part of the ALT tag.

124
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:39,500
The second last tip is about creating a sitemap.

125
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,800
It is something search engines use.

126
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:45,040
It is like a map or road map that helps search engines to figure out where all content is

127
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:50,760
on your website.

128
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:52,880
Sitemaps don't boost search ranking but it does help search engines navigate the content

129
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,800
on your site.

130
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:59,560
Most SEO plugins will generate a sitemap for your site automatically so it is not

131
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:04,640
something you have to code if you are not able to.

132
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,800
Finally, let's talk about local SEO to optimize your site to show higher in local search results.

133
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:15,040
Especially if your customer base is primarily located in the same city or metropolitan area.

134
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:20,720
There are a few things that you can do.

135
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:23,320
Do some local SEO keyword research, add your contact information in your footer or contact

136
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:29,120
page, post localized content and get local backlinks meaning get local sites to refer

137
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:36,880
or link to your site.

138
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:39,280
All the best as you endeavour to improve your own SEO rankings.

139
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:43,400
And don't forget to install and activate an SEO plugin that works best for you.

